editorial:
**State**: `dp[i][j]` = number of paths from (0,0) to (i,j).

**Recurrence**: `dp[i][j] = dp[i-1][j] + dp[i][j-1]` (came from above or from the left).

**Base**: `dp[0][j] = dp[i][0] = 1` (only one straight path along an edge).

```javascript
function uniqueWarehousePaths(m, n) {
  const dp = new Array(n).fill(1);
  for (let i = 1; i < m; i++) {
    for (let j = 1; j < n; j++) {
      dp[j] += dp[j - 1];
    }
  }
  return dp[n - 1];
}
```

**Time**: O(m*n). **Space**: O(n) — rolling 1D array, since each cell only depends on the cell above (old `dp[j]`) and the cell to the left (new `dp[j-1]`).

Closed form `C(m+n-2, m-1)` is O(min(m,n)) time but DP is what an interviewer wants to see.

