editorial:
**State**: `dp[i][j]` = minimum toll cost to reach (i,j).

**Recurrence**: `dp[i][j] = grid[i][j] + min(dp[i-1][j], dp[i][j-1])`.

**Base**: `dp[0][0] = grid[0][0]`; first row is prefix sum of row 0; first column is prefix sum of column 0.

```javascript
function minTollPath(grid) {
  const m = grid.length, n = grid[0].length;
  const dp = new Array(n);
  dp[0] = grid[0][0];
  for (let j = 1; j < n; j++) dp[j] = dp[j-1] + grid[0][j];
  for (let i = 1; i < m; i++) {
    dp[0] += grid[i][0];
    for (let j = 1; j < n; j++) {
      dp[j] = grid[i][j] + Math.min(dp[j], dp[j-1]);
    }
  }
  return dp[n-1];
}
```

**Time**: O(m*n). **Space**: O(n).

