editorial:
**State**: `dp[i][j]` = min edits to turn `s[0..i-1]` into `t[0..j-1]`.

**Recurrence**:
- Match: `dp[i][j] = dp[i-1][j-1]`
- Mismatch: `1 + min(dp[i-1][j-1] /* replace */, dp[i-1][j] /* delete from s */, dp[i][j-1] /* insert into s */)`

**Base**: `dp[0][j] = j` (insert j chars), `dp[i][0] = i` (delete i chars).

```javascript
function editDistance(s, t) {
  const m = s.length, n = t.length;
  const dp = Array.from({length: m + 1}, () => new Array(n + 1).fill(0));
  for (let i = 0; i <= m; i++) dp[i][0] = i;
  for (let j = 0; j <= n; j++) dp[0][j] = j;
  for (let i = 1; i <= m; i++) {
    for (let j = 1; j <= n; j++) {
      dp[i][j] = s[i-1] === t[j-1]
        ? dp[i-1][j-1]
        : 1 + Math.min(dp[i-1][j-1], dp[i-1][j], dp[i][j-1]);
    }
  }
  return dp[m][n];
}
```

**Time**: O(m*n). **Space**: O(m*n) shown; can be reduced to O(min(m,n)) with two rolling rows.

