editorial:
**Why this is a 2-D DP problem**: the general edit-distance DP solves it; we just check `dp[m][n] === 1`. But for *exactly* one edit, an O(min(m,n)) linear scan is cleaner.

**Linear approach**:
1. If `|m - n| > 1`: false.
2. Walk both strings together. At first mismatch: if lengths equal, the suffixes after this index must match. If `s` is shorter, `t`'s remaining tail (skipping its current char) must match `s`'s tail. Symmetric for the other case.
3. If we make it through with no mismatch, return `m !== n` (one trailing-char insert/delete).

```javascript
function isOneEditDistance(s, t) {
  const m = s.length, n = t.length;
  if (Math.abs(m - n) > 1) return false;
  if (m > n) return isOneEditDistance(t, s);
  for (let i = 0; i < m; i++) {
    if (s[i] !== t[i]) {
      if (m === n) return s.slice(i+1) === t.slice(i+1);
      return s.slice(i) === t.slice(i+1);
    }
  }
  return m !== n;
}
```

**Time**: O(m + n). **Space**: O(1) extra (slices aside).

