editorial:
**State**: `dp[i][j]` = minimum scalar multiplications to multiply matrices `i..j` (0-indexed). Matrix `k` has dims `dims[k] x dims[k+1]`.

**Recurrence**: split at `k` between `i` and `j-1`:
`dp[i][j] = min(dp[i][k] + dp[k+1][j] + dims[i] * dims[k+1] * dims[j+1])`.

**Base**: `dp[i][i] = 0` (single matrix needs no multiplication).

```javascript
function matrixChainCost(dims) {
  const n = dims.length - 1;
  const dp = Array.from({length: n}, () => new Array(n).fill(0));
  for (let len = 2; len <= n; len++) {
    for (let i = 0; i + len - 1 < n; i++) {
      const j = i + len - 1;
      let best = Infinity;
      for (let k = i; k < j; k++) {
        const cost = dp[i][k] + dp[k+1][j] + dims[i] * dims[k+1] * dims[j+1];
        if (cost < best) best = cost;
      }
      dp[i][j] = best;
    }
  }
  return dp[0][n-1];
}
```

**Time**: O(n^3). **Space**: O(n^2).

