**State (2-D)**: `dp[i][a]` = ways to form amount `a` using only the first `i` coin types.

**Recurrence**: Either skip coin `i`: `dp[i-1][a]`. Or use at least one coin `i` (it's unlimited): `dp[i][a - coins[i-1]]`. So `dp[i][a] = dp[i-1][a] + dp[i][a - coins[i-1]]` when `a >= coins[i-1]`.

